eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Female sex
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Female

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Age requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Aged 25-55 years.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Willingness to follow study protocols
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Willing to follow the study protocols.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Self-reported skin issues
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Self-reported issues with at least two of the following: Fine lines, Wrinkles, Hyperpigmentation, Dark spots, Reduced elasticity

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Self-reported neck and chest concerns
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Self-report concerns with at least one of the following: Crepey skin on the neck and chest, Sun damage on neck and chest

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Willingness to avoid new skin health products
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Willing to avoid introducing any new products, prescription medications, or supplements that target skin health during the study period.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Consistent oral supplement use
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: If taking oral supplements or herbal remedies targeted at skin health and appearance, have been consistently taking these for at least 3 months prior to starting the study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Willingness to maintain supplement routine
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Is willing to maintain the routine of any oral supplements or herbal remedies targeted at skin health and appearance for the duration of the study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Consistent skincare routine
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Has been using the same skincare routine for at least one month prior to the study start date.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Willingness to maintain skincare routine
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Willing to maintain the same skincare routine and products throughout the study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Willingness to avoid direct sun exposure
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Willing to avoid direct sun exposure during the study duration

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Willingness to wear sunscreen
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Willing to wear sunscreen if have to be in the sun

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Extremely satisfied with skin
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who is extremely satisfied with their skin.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Chronic health conditions
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who has any chronic health conditions such as oncological (cancer) or psychiatric disorders.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Planned or recent facial treatments
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who is planning to undergo facial treatments during the study period, including botox, dermal filler, chemical peels, etc. or has experienced any of these treatments in the last 3 months.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Diagnosed skin condition with recent flare-up
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone diagnosed with a skin condition affecting the face and/or neck who has had an active flare-up or breakout within the last year. This includes but is not limited to acne, eczema, psoriasis, rosacea, seborrheic dermatitis, vitiligo, urticaria (hives), warts, atopic dermatitis, melasma, and contact dermatitis.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prescription medications affecting skin
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Currently using any prescription medications that may affect the skin condition including but not limited to the following: Corticosteroids like prednisone, methylprednisolone; Antipsychotics like olanzapine (Zyprexa), risperidone (Risperdal), quetiapine (Seroquel); SSRIs and SNRIs like fluoxetine (Prozac), sertraline (Zoloft), venlafaxine (Effexor); Anticonvulsants like phenytoin (Dilantin), lamotrigine (Lamictal), and carbamazepine (Tegretol); Antihypertensives like lisinopril (Zestril), amlodipine (Norvasc), and propranolol (Inderal); Antithyroid medications like Tapazole (methimazole), Propyl-Thyracil (propylthiouracil)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: History of skin cancer or precancerous lesions
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone with a history of skin cancer or precancerous skin lesions on the face.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Serious allergic reactions requiring Epi-Pen
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who has any known serious allergic reactions that require the use of an Epi-Pen.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Allergies to skincare product ingredients
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who has any known allergies to ingredients commonly found in skincare products.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Pregnant, breastfeeding, or trying to conceive
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or trying to conceive

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Cannot commit to study protocol
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who cannot/will not commit to the study protocol.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: History of substance abuse
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone with a history of substance abuse.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Recent or planned invasive medical procedure
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who has undergone an invasive medical procedure in the three weeks prior to the study or has a procedure planned during the study duration.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Allergic reaction to aluminum or plastics
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone with a known allergic reaction to aluminum or plastics.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Photosensitive disorder
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who suffers from any photosensitive disorder (sensitization to light).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Uncontrolled acne
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone with uncontrolled acne.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Photosensitizing medications or supplements
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone taking any prescription medication, over-the-counter supplements, or herbal supplements regularly (three or more days per week) that can cause photosensitivity including but not limited to the following: Antibiotics like tetracyclines (e.g., doxycycline, tetracycline) or sulfonamides (e.g., Bactrim), fluoroquinolones (e.g., ciprofloxacin, levofloxacin); Antifungals like Griseofulvin or Vfend (voriconazole); Diuretics like drugs ending in -thiazides; NSAIDs like ibuprofen and Aleve (naproxen); Retinoids or Vitamin A (e.g., Accutane (isotretinoin), (Retin-A) tretinoin; Antidepressants (e.g., SSRIs, Elavil (amitriptyline), Tofranil (imipramine); Antihistamines like Phenergan (promethazine); Antimalarial medications; Statins like Lipitor (atorvastatin), Zocor (simvastatin); Antiarrhythmics like Pacerone (amiodarone); St. John's wort

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Light-induced headaches or migraines
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who suffers from light-induced headaches or migraines.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: History of seizures or epilepsy triggered by light
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone with a medical history of seizures or epilepsy triggered by light.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Electronic implanted device
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone with an electronic implanted device such as a defibrillator, neurostimulator, pacemaker, or ECG monitor.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: History of carotid artery disease or related conditions
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone with a known history of carotid artery disease, stroke or transient ischemic attack (TIA), carotid stenosis, unstable blood pressure, easy fainting, thyroid disease, or of individuals about to undergo surgical procedures in the neck area.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Recent discontinuation of hormonal birth control
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Anyone who has stopped hormonal birth control in the past month.
